Incident.Summary: CT 180585848. Microsoft Bing reverse-image search. Cecil Co.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Attachments

-NCMEC Cybertip #180585848

 

Narrative

On 11/27/23, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # 180585848. The Cyber Tip, generated by Microsoft, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip was assigned to Senior Trooper Cooke #6272 for investigation.

 

The CyberTip provided the following information pertaining to the suspect:

 

IP Address: 2601:145:c301:c860:e86e:e8d1:a382:57d6
11-27-2023 04:31:50 UTC
Additional Information: BingImage (referred to as Visual Search) is a service that provides similar images to an image provided by the user. This image can be provided either via upload or as a URL. The DateTime provided indicates the time at which the image was received and evaluated by the BingImage service. Please note the information contained in this CyberTip is the only information related to this user in Microsoft systems. All reportable information has been submitted and there is no other information regarding this user that can be supplied through additional legal process.

 

The CyberTip contained 1 reported child pornography file. S/T Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography file and determined that it constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below:

 

Filename: 7ed81aba-022c-4a8f-ac74-50225968f6a7.jpg

Description: image file showing a fully nude white female exposing her genitals in a lewd and lascivious manner. The female is reasonably believed to be between 7 - 9 years of age; she is flat-chested, lacks overall development, and lacks pubic hair.

 

 

The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 2601:145:c301:c860:e86e:e8d1:a382:57d6 (11-27-2023 04:31:50 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband file.

 

S/T Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Comcast Cable and geo-locates generally to the Elkton area of Cecil County, Maryland.

 

S/T Cooke transmitted an investigative subpoena request to the Anne Arundel County Office of the State’s Attorney for Comcast subscriber information.

 

Case Status

OPEN / PENDING ADDITIONAL INVESTIGATION
